00:47.921 --> 00:50.723
Whoa... hey, dude,
are you all right?

00:52.092 --> 00:54.293
Whoa, wh-wh-what
happened to your face?

00:54.327 --> 00:56.395
I fell, okay?

00:56.429 --> 00:58.349
The stupid janitor didn't
put salt on the ramp,

00:58.350 --> 01:00.590
like he's supposed to, and
my wheels don't have chains,

01:00.591 --> 01:04.470
so I slipped backwards and
tipped over on the ice.

01:04.504 --> 01:05.738
It's fine. It's nothing.

01:05.772 --> 01:07.206
No, no, no, no...
hey, hey, hey.

01:07.240 --> 01:08.640
That's not nothing.

01:08.675 --> 01:10.609
That's some pretty serious road rash.

01:10.643 --> 01:12.643
Let me take you to
the nurse's office, all right?

01:18.451 --> 01:20.586
You hit your head pretty hard.

01:20.620 --> 01:22.154
I'm going to go call your mother.

01:22.188 --> 01:24.089
Lay down till she gets here.

01:24.124 --> 01:26.892
Want me to help you get
up on the cot? No.

01:26.926 --> 01:28.927
I don't want anybody
to help me with anything.

01:28.962 --> 01:30.596
I'm tired of being so helpless,

01:30.630 --> 01:32.297
I'm tired of everybody pitying me,

01:32.332 --> 01:34.166
and I'm tired of being
in this damn chair.

01:34.200 --> 01:36.602
Anyone could have fallen
on the ice, all right?

01:36.636 --> 01:38.196
Yeah, but they could've gotten back up,

01:38.197 --> 01:39.917
instead of laying there
screaming for help

01:39.918 --> 01:41.406
until some freshman girl showed up.

01:41.441 --> 01:43.675
Dude, don't bite my head off.

01:43.710 --> 01:45.410
But you need some rest,

01:45.445 --> 01:47.346
so I'm going to help
you out, all right?

01:59.192 --> 02:02.294
I just wish I was never
in that dumb chair.

02:02.328 --> 02:04.830
I know, buddy. I know.

02:44.871 --> 02:46.338
Tina!

02:46.372 --> 02:48.140
Look.

02:48.174 --> 02:50.142
Can you believe it?

02:50.176 --> 02:52.878
Believe what?

02:52.912 --> 02:55.514
Why are you stuttering again?

02:55.548 --> 02:58.483
She never stopped because
you never became friends.

02:58.518 --> 03:00.385
Rory?!

03:00.420 --> 03:01.887
What are you doing here?

03:01.921 --> 03:03.922
And talk slowly,
so I can understand you.

03:03.957 --> 03:06.692
I'm your Christmas guardian angel.

03:06.726 --> 03:07.993
And I've granted your wish.

03:08.027 --> 03:10.162
Your car accident never happened.

03:10.196 --> 03:12.664
You were never in that dumb chair.

03:12.699 --> 03:14.566
That's insane.

03:14.601 --> 03:15.834
Don't believe me?

03:15.869 --> 03:17.502
Ask Becky.

03:17.537 --> 03:19.371
Merry Christmas, stud.

03:19.405 --> 03:22.941
Want to fool around?
I can't get pregnant.

03:22.976 --> 03:24.743
What? No.

03:26.412 --> 03:28.347
Becky's the school slut now.

03:28.381 --> 03:30.015
No one treats her with any respect.

03:30.049 --> 03:31.683
But I do.
I took her on a date.

03:31.718 --> 03:33.252
No, you didn't.

03:33.286 --> 03:35.166
You were too busy throwing
losers in Dumpsters

03:35.167 --> 03:37.327
to give her any attention
or treat her with kindness,

03:37.328 --> 03:40.058
and as a result, she never
learned any self-respect.

03:40.093 --> 03:42.261
Hey! Hey, Kurt!
Nice cape!

03:42.295 --> 03:43.975
Who are you supposed
to be... Super Homo?

03:43.976 --> 03:45.364
What are you guys doing?

03:45.398 --> 03:48.433
Just having some fun
with Little Lord Gay Boy.

03:48.468 --> 03:50.569
But you guys
aren't straight douche bags.

03:50.603 --> 03:52.170
You sang Lady Gaga songs.

03:54.140 --> 03:55.741
Keep telling those dirty lies,

03:55.775 --> 03:57.910
and we'll break your friggin' legs.

04:07.587 --> 04:09.421
Kurt, didn't you graduate?

04:09.455 --> 04:12.438
I should've, but I couldn't
bear coming to school

04:12.439 --> 04:14.559
more than twice a week,
because of all the bullying.

04:14.594 --> 04:17.428
All the homeschooling
set me back a year.

04:17.463 --> 04:18.930
What does Blaine say about that?

04:18.964 --> 04:21.166
Who's Blaine?

04:23.202 --> 04:25.170
Mr. Shue,
thank God you're here.

04:25.204 --> 04:27.472
We need to call an emergency
meeting of the glee club.

04:27.507 --> 04:28.588
What glee club?

04:28.589 --> 04:30.429
I couldn't get enough
of you brats interested

04:30.430 --> 04:31.910
to get that lame idea off the ground.

04:31.945 --> 04:33.945
Will, I need your paycheck
before you blow it all

04:33.946 --> 04:35.363
on booze and flannel shirts.

04:35.364 --> 04:37.364
Sheets and Things is having
a big Christmas sale,

04:37.365 --> 04:38.925
and we desperately need an air purifier

04:38.926 --> 04:40.686
for our moldy garbage heap
of an apartment.

04:40.720 --> 04:42.454
That's a doll.
Shh!

04:42.488 --> 04:44.328
He's so drunk he doesn't
know the difference.

04:45.558 --> 04:47.659
You're cute.

04:47.694 --> 04:49.861
Where's Miss Pillsbury?

04:49.896 --> 04:51.163
In Hawaii.

04:51.197 --> 04:53.432
With her dear, sweet
husband Coach Tanaka.

04:53.466 --> 04:55.367
It's a match made
in heaven, right, honey?

04:55.401 --> 04:56.868
That's right.

05:10.683 --> 05:13.051
Rachel?
What are you doing here?

05:13.086 --> 05:15.206
You live in New York.
You go to the most prestigious

05:15.207 --> 05:16.455
drama school in the country.

05:16.489 --> 05:18.957
Well, I am gonna be in
the Lima Community Players'

05:18.992 --> 05:20.692
production of <i>The Music Man.</i>

05:20.727 --> 05:22.887
Tell me you're at least playing
Marian the Librarian.

05:22.888 --> 05:24.896
No, that's the lead.
I'm just in the chorus.

05:24.931 --> 05:26.531
Excuse me.

05:26.566 --> 05:27.566
Rachel...

05:27.600 --> 05:29.234
what's going on?
Let go of me!

05:29.268 --> 05:31.169
What happened you?
What happened to all of us?

05:32.071 --> 05:32.904
- Hey!
- No!

05:37.176 --> 05:39.378
Rory! Rory, where are you?

05:39.412 --> 05:41.079
What's wrong?

05:41.114 --> 05:42.147
What's wrong?!

05:42.181 --> 05:43.548
Everything.

05:43.583 --> 05:44.983
How can everything be so messed up?

05:44.984 --> 05:46.418
You weren't in a wheelchair,

05:46.452 --> 05:49.221
so you were too busy
playing football to join Glee.

05:50.089 --> 05:51.723
It turns out...

05:51.758 --> 05:54.326
you were the glue of Glee, Artie.

05:54.360 --> 05:57.329
The quiet, steady,
beating heart of the group.

05:57.363 --> 06:00.365
No glue... no Glee.

06:00.400 --> 06:01.400
I can fix this.

06:01.434 --> 06:02.868
I can.

06:02.902 --> 06:04.182
I'll get them all back together.

06:04.183 --> 06:06.038
Just you watch, I'll fix it.

06:06.072 --> 06:07.232
You're probably wondering why

06:07.233 --> 06:09.193
I've asked you all
to meet me in the choir room.

06:09.194 --> 06:10.942
This is Coach Sue's craft room.

06:10.977 --> 06:13.345
Well, in an alternate universe,
it was the choir room.

06:13.379 --> 06:15.514
I had a dream about that once.
I know.

06:15.548 --> 06:17.582
And it was a place that
always made me feel safe.

06:17.617 --> 06:19.785
And I know it did
for a lot of you, too.

06:19.819 --> 06:22.254
That's 'cause we danced
together, we sang together,

06:22.288 --> 06:23.455
we took turns up here.

06:23.489 --> 06:24.536
Like Finn said,

06:24.537 --> 06:25.857
it's about the love of the music.

06:25.892 --> 06:26.858
Dude, are you high?

06:26.893 --> 06:28.360
I never said that.

06:28.394 --> 06:30.796
