09:28.808 --> 09:30.642
You know, I could use some help here.

09:33.746 --> 09:36.114
Come on, grab onto me.

09:38.451 --> 09:40.752
Sorry, Artie.

09:40.786 --> 09:44.623
I know it really sucks being
in this chair sometimes.

09:44.657 --> 09:47.325
For better or for worse,
this chair is a part of me.

09:47.360 --> 09:49.361
It's made me who I am.

09:56.678 --> 09:58.646
Well, if you're not
going to come to Lima,

09:58.680 --> 10:00.681
then my dads and I
insist you come with us

10:00.715 --> 10:02.883
to the Rosie O'Donnell
Gay Holiday Cruise.

10:02.918 --> 10:04.085
It's going to be so much fun.

10:04.119 --> 10:05.093
There's even going to be

10:05.094 --> 10:06.854
a Jessie Tyler Ferguson
look-alike contest.

10:06.888 --> 10:08.222
Well, in that case,

10:08.256 --> 10:09.757
I'm definitely gonna have to pass.

10:09.791 --> 10:10.972
Honey, uh...
And besides,

10:10.973 --> 10:12.893
there's really no reason
to go to Lima, anyway.

10:12.928 --> 10:14.436
My dad and Finn and Carole

10:14.437 --> 10:16.197
are visiting Carole's
sister in Zanesville,

10:16.198 --> 10:18.238
and she always has too much
eggnog and blacks out.

10:18.239 --> 10:18.839
Happy holidays!

10:18.840 --> 10:20.167
Well, what about Blaine?

10:20.202 --> 10:22.203
I talk to him.

10:22.237 --> 10:23.671
But, you know, he knows

10:23.705 --> 10:25.406
that I'm saving my money for NYADA now.

10:25.440 --> 10:27.560
And it'll be good to just
have some time for myself,

10:27.561 --> 10:29.510
you know, and think about things and...

10:30.912 --> 10:32.279
Can you get that?

10:32.314 --> 10:34.281
Okay, what do we need for this tree?

10:34.316 --> 10:36.283
It's just hopeless...

10:39.121 --> 10:40.354
Dad!

10:41.556 --> 10:42.590
Burt?

10:42.624 --> 10:44.225
Season's greetings!

10:44.259 --> 10:45.459
Oh, my God!

10:45.494 --> 10:46.934
Well, I got a tree...
you need one?

10:46.935 --> 10:48.028
Come in!

10:48.063 --> 10:49.763
Okay, all right.
I got it, I got it.

10:52.400 --> 10:54.802
Okay, you can let go now.

10:54.836 --> 10:56.103
Okay.

10:56.138 --> 10:57.605
Come on, let's go look at it.

10:59.574 --> 11:01.775
Oh, it's perfect.

11:01.810 --> 11:03.370
Yeah, well, I couldn't imagine you guys

11:03.371 --> 11:05.091
celebrating Christmas
without a real tree.

11:05.092 --> 11:07.548
You know, his mom used
to always buy the tree.

11:07.582 --> 11:08.942
I'd always tell her to wait till I

11:08.943 --> 11:10.583
got home from work,
but she never could.

11:10.585 --> 11:12.887
And then, the first Christmas
after his mom died,

11:12.921 --> 11:15.322
I totally forgot about it.

11:15.357 --> 11:17.091
That is, until

11:17.125 --> 11:18.492
I saw little Kurt

11:18.527 --> 11:19.994
hanging his own special version

11:20.028 --> 11:21.295
of a Christmas ornament

11:21.329 --> 11:23.330
on his window shade Christmas Eve.

11:25.033 --> 11:27.268
My mom's perfume bottle.

11:27.302 --> 11:28.936
Oh, I always loved the way she smelled.

11:28.970 --> 11:30.638
So I pull him out of bed,

11:30.672 --> 11:31.859
I throw a coat on him,

11:31.860 --> 11:33.340
I drive straight through a snowstorm,

11:33.375 --> 11:35.109
right down to the Christmas tree sale.

11:35.143 --> 11:39.513
It was the first time he
smiled since his mom died.

11:41.449 --> 11:44.418
Okay, no tears on Christmas Eve.

11:44.452 --> 11:46.787
This box is full
of happy memories, as well.

11:46.821 --> 11:48.522
Like our Christmas trip to Dollywood.

11:48.557 --> 11:50.024
Oh, yeah.
That one I like.

11:50.058 --> 11:51.158
That trip was for me.

11:51.193 --> 11:52.927
Oh, and this redneck NASCAR trip,

11:52.961 --> 11:55.429
that was for you. Hey,
this is a nice ornament.

11:55.463 --> 11:57.164
Let's hang them.

11:57.199 --> 11:59.466
All right, well, I wish I could stay,

11:59.501 --> 12:01.835
but can't really be late
for a cruise, so...

12:01.870 --> 12:03.830
Oh, hold on. You got to
open this before you go.

12:03.831 --> 12:06.240
Uh, happy Hanukkah, merry Christmas.

12:09.344 --> 12:12.379
It's for your first
New York holiday season.

12:12.414 --> 12:13.981
Hang it together.
Thank you.

12:14.015 --> 12:15.816
And then you can go.
Okay.

12:17.252 --> 12:20.154
Kurt, okay, this, to our very first.

12:20.188 --> 12:22.156
New York Christmas.

12:24.059 --> 12:26.060
Ha. I never thought
I'd see this day.

12:26.094 --> 12:27.995
Us walking down the
streets of New York,

12:28.029 --> 12:30.130
right after seeing a
live Broadway musical.

12:30.165 --> 12:32.399
Well, the Rockettes
might have better legs than me,

12:32.434 --> 12:34.668
but they can't touch
my "Single Ladies" performance.

12:34.703 --> 12:36.637
That was the best
musical I've ever seen.

12:36.671 --> 12:37.905
Ah, it's freezing!

12:37.939 --> 12:39.907
I think it's time to check off another.

12:39.941 --> 12:43.544
Hummel family tradition:
Hot chocolate.

12:48.550 --> 12:50.017
Kurt, I have something to tell you,

12:50.051 --> 12:51.999
and I came here
because it's the kind of thing

12:52.000 --> 12:53.320
I want to tell you
face-to-face.

12:53.355 --> 12:54.515
Don't like the sound of that.

12:54.522 --> 12:56.023
Look, I'm just going to

12:56.057 --> 12:58.025
come out and say it
because there's no...

12:58.059 --> 12:59.727
good way to say it.

12:59.761 --> 13:02.896
Uh, I have prostate cancer.

13:07.235 --> 13:09.436
Feel like I'm going to be sick.

13:09.471 --> 13:10.704
No, no, hey, hey, look at me.

13:10.739 --> 13:12.072
Do I look like a guy who's dying?

13:12.107 --> 13:13.540
We caught it early.

13:13.575 --> 13:16.010
You know, local stage, no spreading.

13:16.044 --> 13:18.212
Cure rate's nearly 100%.

13:18.246 --> 13:20.247
For healthy people, Dad.

13:20.282 --> 13:21.642
You've already had a heart attack.

13:21.643 --> 13:23.083
The heart attack is what, you know,

13:23.118 --> 13:26.120
made me get checkups twice a year.

13:26.154 --> 13:29.256
It's just really scary to think

13:29.291 --> 13:33.560
that when I finally reach my destiny,

13:33.595 --> 13:35.896
that you won't be around to see it.

13:35.930 --> 13:36.964
Hey.

13:37.999 --> 13:39.933
I will be there.

13:39.968 --> 13:42.069
I promise.

13:46.274 --> 13:48.909
Look, can I just give you
one piece of advice

13:48.943 --> 13:52.046
while we're still talking
father to son?

13:52.080 --> 13:55.949
This is three times I've had
to stare death in the eye.

13:55.984 --> 13:58.552
And you know the one thing
I took away from all that?

13:58.586 --> 14:00.421
You have got to hold
the people you love

14:00.455 --> 14:01.955
close to you no matter what.

14:10.598 --> 14:12.800
Dad, you okay?

14:12.834 --> 14:15.569
Do you need a pillow or tea, water?

14:15.603 --> 14:16.837
No, Kurt, stop.

14:16.871 --> 14:19.340
Come on, let's focus on happy things.

14:19.374 --> 14:21.842
Like our Christmas traditions.

14:21.876 --> 14:25.446
I am looking forward to watching
basketball on Christmas Day

14:25.480 --> 14:27.948
while you pretend you watch with me.

14:27.982 --> 14:29.917
You mean while I secretly read <i>Vogue?</i>

14:29.951 --> 14:31.352
That was never a secret.

14:31.386 --> 14:33.520
No, like our other
Christmas traditions.

14:33.555 --> 14:36.256
Like on Christmas Eve,
where we each exchange one gift.

14:36.291 --> 14:38.025
My favorite part.

14:38.059 --> 14:39.360
All right, you first.

14:39.394 --> 14:41.295
Ah, I saw that.

14:42.297 --> 14:44.798
Nice.

14:44.833 --> 14:46.713
I know it's cheesy, but
thought you'd like it.

14:46.735 --> 14:48.602
Screw cheesy. I love it.

14:48.636 --> 14:51.338
In <i>México,</i> they would
call me Señor Queso.

14:51.373 --> 14:53.474
Look at this. Ah, man.

14:53.508 --> 14:55.309
I love it, man.

14:55.343 --> 14:57.711
You are going to kick ass
at that school.

14:57.746 --> 15:00.547
That's the plan.

15:00.582 --> 15:02.383
All right, my turn.

15:02.417 --> 15:05.152
Okay, so my gift to you is really big.

15:05.186 --> 15:06.854
It's too big to put under the tree.

15:06.888 --> 15:08.288
Curiosity piqued.

15:08.323 --> 15:11.024
Okay, so you can pick it up
at this address,

15:11.059 --> 15:13.227
and, you know, if you don't like it,

15:13.261 --> 15:14.695
you can return it.

15:25.006 --> 15:27.474
