30:27.839 --> 30:29.506
to become your Mayan star-wife.

30:29.541 --> 30:31.041
You may kiss your bride.

30:41.386 --> 30:43.153
It's December 18.

30:43.188 --> 30:44.788
Three days till the end.

30:46.424 --> 30:47.858
Let's make this time count.

30:57.569 --> 30:59.970
Brittany.

31:00.005 --> 31:01.805
It's December 22.

31:03.708 --> 31:05.876
We survived the Mayan Apocalypse.

31:05.910 --> 31:07.778
You know what this means?

31:07.812 --> 31:09.013
The world didn't end.

31:09.047 --> 31:11.048
We're also married.

31:17.959 --> 31:19.893
You know, I hate to ask you something

31:19.927 --> 31:21.461
during your midday ritual of devouring

31:21.496 --> 31:23.663
an entire animal carcass,
so here goes nothing.

31:23.698 --> 31:25.131
What's going on here?

31:25.166 --> 31:27.801
It's the faculty and staff
Secret Santa!

31:27.835 --> 31:30.504
And you really couldn't
swallow first, could you?

31:34.509 --> 31:35.742
Millie Rose.

31:35.776 --> 31:37.244
Who the hell's Millie Rose?

31:37.278 --> 31:40.347
She's a sweetheart.
She works in the cafeteria.

31:40.381 --> 31:45.085
She's a big lady, and I think
her daughter's in the glee club.

31:48.723 --> 31:50.857
How about this one?

32:00.234 --> 32:02.936
Becky, it's a beautiful
sweater from Benetton.

32:02.970 --> 32:04.204
Epic fail!

32:04.238 --> 32:06.706
I already got one of these, Coach!

32:06.741 --> 32:09.109
Get me something I don't already have!

32:09.143 --> 32:11.344
Like what?
Like a hot date!

32:11.379 --> 32:14.014
Or a snowmobile!

32:14.048 --> 32:16.483
Oh, Becky, you're not the only
person I have to shop for.

32:16.517 --> 32:19.286
I got to get something for that
hideous wad of a lunch lady,

32:19.320 --> 32:21.388
who somehow was able to squeeze out

32:21.422 --> 32:23.723
a ravishing,
golden-throated,

32:23.758 --> 32:27.027
raven-haired beauty from
those monstrous, gaping loins.

32:28.763 --> 32:31.831
What do you get the woman
who's eaten everything?

32:33.267 --> 32:36.570
Just to be clear,
no presents this year.

32:36.604 --> 32:38.004
That money is going to a therapist

32:38.039 --> 32:39.839
who specializes in eating disorders.

32:39.874 --> 32:41.474
We're not playing around here.

32:41.509 --> 32:42.576
I know, Mom.

32:42.610 --> 32:44.077
I know this is serious.

32:44.111 --> 32:47.380
I have a problem,
and I want to get better.

32:47.415 --> 32:50.984
Besides, we don't really need anything.

32:51.018 --> 32:52.319
Not even a tree?

32:52.353 --> 32:54.487
Marley...

32:54.522 --> 32:56.723
a tree is $50,

32:56.757 --> 33:00.093
and a session with
Dr. Goodsitt is $200.

33:00.127 --> 33:03.096
I don't need to tell you that
I don't make a lot of money.

33:03.130 --> 33:05.265
I will be damned if
I waste a penny of it

33:05.299 --> 33:07.200
before my daughter is healthy enough

33:07.234 --> 33:10.036
to realize what
a beautiful miracle she is.

33:13.708 --> 33:16.042
Sorry.

33:16.077 --> 33:18.445
If you want to give me a gift,

33:18.479 --> 33:20.880
sing me something.

33:22.583 --> 33:24.150
Deal.

33:27.254 --> 33:32.926
♪ The first Noel ♪

33:32.960 --> 33:35.695
♪ The angel did say ♪

33:35.730 --> 33:40.600
♪ Was to certain poor shepherds ♪

33:40.635 --> 33:44.704
♪ In fields as they lay ♪

33:44.739 --> 33:48.642
♪ Noel, Noel ♪

33:48.676 --> 33:51.276
♪ Noel, Noel... ♪

33:56.851 --> 34:02.622
♪ Born is the king ♪

34:02.657 --> 34:04.657
♪ Of Israel. ♪

34:08.763 --> 34:10.897
That, right there,

34:10.931 --> 34:14.467
is the best Christmas gift
I have ever gotten.

34:24.277 --> 34:25.745
Well, Becky,

34:25.780 --> 34:27.914
I feel absolutely horrible.

34:27.947 --> 34:30.583
I've become selfish and spoiled,

34:30.618 --> 34:32.752
and incredibly out of touch.

34:32.786 --> 34:34.120
Look at this tree.

34:34.155 --> 34:36.489
Yes, it has a stark beauty all its own.

34:36.524 --> 34:38.591
But did I really need to cut down

34:38.626 --> 34:41.161
a 7,000-year-old
bristlecone pine

34:41.195 --> 34:43.096
just to hang ornaments on it?

34:43.130 --> 34:45.098
It just seems frivolous.

34:45.132 --> 34:47.033
Becky, I just made a call

34:47.068 --> 34:48.768
to a guy in the antiquities business.

34:48.803 --> 34:52.304
He's got contacts in the
luxury toothpick market.

34:52.339 --> 34:54.007
You and I are gonna sell him this tree,

34:54.041 --> 34:55.809
and we're going to give the proceeds

34:55.842 --> 34:59.479
to a very important cause.

35:01.916 --> 35:03.983
Marley? Marley!

35:04.018 --> 35:06.419
Marley, get down here, sweetie.

35:10.725 --> 35:12.158
Oh, my God.

35:12.193 --> 35:13.860
I know.

35:13.894 --> 35:15.470
Yeah, the back door was jimmied open,

35:15.471 --> 35:17.831
I was gonna call the police,
and then I saw all this. Mom.

35:17.865 --> 35:19.466
Look at this sweater.

35:19.500 --> 35:21.234
It's... I think
it's from Benetton.

35:21.268 --> 35:22.836
Oh, sweet Lord...

35:24.672 --> 35:27.540
I am gonna pass out. Marley...
Oh, my God.

35:27.575 --> 35:29.042
Marley, there's $800 here.

35:29.076 --> 35:31.311
Oh, my God.

35:31.345 --> 35:33.980
Merry Christmas, Mom!

35:34.014 --> 35:36.416
Merry Christmas, sweetheart.

35:41.889 --> 35:44.758
We should probably
still call the police.

35:47.323 --> 35:49.043
I actually think I
knew it was really over

35:49.044 --> 35:51.426
when he tried to pick
up on my sister...

35:51.460 --> 35:53.662
at her baby shower.

35:55.965 --> 35:58.542
Aw, look at 'em.

35:58.578 --> 36:01.914
Laughing, trading war
stories about us kids.

36:01.948 --> 36:04.083
It's a true Hanukkah miracle.

36:04.117 --> 36:07.286
You know, I'm really gonna miss
you when you go back to L.A.

36:08.555 --> 36:10.656
I was thinking about that.

36:10.690 --> 36:12.925
I mean, I'm a screenwriter.
I can write anywhere.

36:12.959 --> 36:15.561
And I'm sure most of my
pool-cleaning clients in Lima

36:15.595 --> 36:16.862
would take me back, so...

36:16.896 --> 36:18.197
So you're moving back home?

36:18.231 --> 36:20.733
L.A. is great, but...

36:20.767 --> 36:23.035
someone needs to look
after you and our moms.

36:25.438 --> 36:27.206
So we're not actually married.

36:27.240 --> 36:30.342
There aren't actually
any Mayan church Web sites.

36:30.377 --> 36:32.244
The Mayans were wiped out 500 years ago

36:32.278 --> 36:34.513
by the conquistadors and smallpox.

36:34.547 --> 36:36.749
That's like chickenpox, but smaller.

36:36.783 --> 36:39.051
Look, when I heard the two
of you were getting engaged,

36:39.066 --> 36:40.786
I thought to myself,
these kids are two...

36:40.820 --> 36:43.789
special kids.

36:43.823 --> 36:46.925
The last thing we need
is another teen tragedy

36:46.960 --> 36:48.560
of marrying too young,

36:48.595 --> 36:50.683
popping out a couple kids
before you're 20

36:50.684 --> 36:52.364
and ending up with
your faces blurred out

36:52.399 --> 36:53.799
on an episode of <i>Cops.</i>

36:53.833 --> 36:55.534
I'm happy to have more time with Sam.

36:55.568 --> 36:57.608
I just... I feel empty
since the world didn't end.

36:57.609 --> 37:00.406
Yeah, like everything
was just so energized

37:00.440 --> 37:03.108
for those few days, and I felt
so close to everyone, and...

37:03.143 --> 37:06.078
It... it was really awesome.
I just miss that feeling.

37:08.440 --> 37:09.915
Hey, look at my phone.

37:09.941 --> 37:13.043
Huh. I got a Google alert
about the Mayan calendar.

37:13.078 --> 37:14.578
It says, uh...

37:14.621 --> 37:17.314
some archaeologist named Indiana Jones

37:17.348 --> 37:19.283
found a new Mayan calendar today.

37:19.325 --> 37:21.151
That's remarkable.

37:21.186 --> 37:24.054
Dr. Jones said that the new
end of the world date

37:24.089 --> 37:27.624
is September 27, 2014.

37:27.659 --> 37:29.019
That gives us like two whole years

37:29.020 --> 37:31.220
of giving love and brutal
honesty to everyone we know.

37:36.267 --> 37:37.468
So, who's winning?

37:37.502 --> 37:39.703
Celtics.
Celtics.

37:52.550 --> 37:54.585
Okay, I tried.

37:54.619 --> 37:56.954
Ah... 20 seconds.
Oh!

37:56.988 --> 37:58.789
Pay up, Anderson.

37:58.823 --> 38:00.924
You may have dated him,
but I raised him.

38:00.959 --> 38:02.627
I know my son.

38:02.628 --> 38:04.308
Aw, you couldn't have
just toughed it out

38:04.309 --> 38:05.669
for just a few more seconds, Kurt?

38:05.670 --> 38:06.830
No.
Just a few more seconds.

38:06.865 --> 38:08.665
So... graduating...

38:08.700 --> 38:10.100
Plans for the future?

38:10.135 --> 38:11.468
Uh... well...

38:11.503 --> 38:13.023
I haven't talked about this with Kurt,

38:13.024 --> 38:14.104
and I wouldn't do anything

38:14.139 --> 38:15.339
to make him uncomfortable,

38:15.373 --> 38:17.007
but I was thinking about

38:17.041 --> 38:18.842
applying to NYADA.

38:18.877 --> 38:20.744
Would that be okay?

38:22.013 --> 38:23.714
I think that'd be great.

38:26.151 --> 38:27.451
Me, too.

38:29.587 --> 38:31.227
Could I talk to you
for a second, Coach?

38:32.991 --> 38:35.826
I wanted to say thank you

38:35.860 --> 38:38.228
for what you did for Marley and me.

38:38.263 --> 38:39.943
I have no idea
what you're talking about.

38:39.978 --> 38:41.978
I had nothing to do
with the making of that film.

38:41.979 --> 38:43.339
I bribed Becky Jackson with candy,

38:43.340 --> 38:44.735
and she told me everything.

38:44.769 --> 38:46.370
You're very generous,

38:46.404 --> 38:49.873
but, um...

38:49.908 --> 38:54.478
I'm afraid I can't accept this money.

38:54.512 --> 38:56.213
Well, you and I both know

38:56.247 --> 38:58.115
how hard it is to be a single mother.

38:59.551 --> 39:02.153
So take the money,

39:02.154 --> 39:04.154
and make sure that daughter
of yours gets better.

39:04.189 --> 39:06.356
Is that understood?

39:06.391 --> 39:08.158
Now, if you'll excuse me,

39:08.193 --> 39:12.563
